The effect of the title “Vintage of the Century” which has been bestowed on the 59s, has created enough buying pres- sure to denude the cellars, despite the large crop. Most were soundly made, are perfect today and display great charm and delicacy. If you want to drink great red Burgundy, vibrantly alive with fruit and charm, drink these for the next few years—and you will match wine pleasure of a pre- vious generation, who were equally lucky with the 1934s— a vintage similar in its character.
